						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar, western second row, <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of Sāntanāyagi shrine, Miharāruṇēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Records that Śōlai Sāttaṉ, a native of Kāñjirikkai-vāralūr in Pāṇḍināḍu made a gift for a drum <hi rend="italic">(timilai)</hi> etc., to the god Mūlaśthānam-uḍaiya mahādēvar in Tirumiyachchūr in Ambar-nāḍu.</p>						

